# START HERE \'97 CONNECT!\
\
---\
\
# PROJECT OVERVIEW\
\
Project name:\
Connect!\
\
What we are building:\
A social sports platform that connects players, coaches, venues, and communities into one seamless ecosystem.\
\
Mission:\
Make sports more social, accessible, and connected for the next generation.\
\
Current stage:\
MVP design and early product development\
\
---\
\
# TARGET USERS\
\
Primary users:\
- urban sports enthusiasts\
- casual and intermediate athletes\
- users looking for sports partners\
- users seeking coaches and skill improvement\
- users looking for convenient venue booking\
- social-first fitness and sports users\
- users interested in sports communities and events\
- competitive and consistency-driven users\
- users seeking real-world social connections through sports\
\
Pain points:\
- difficulty finding sports partners and teammates\
- lack of motivation and consistency\
- fragmented sports communities and communication\
- complicated and time-consuming venue booking\
- difficulty finding trusted coaches\
- disconnected sports experiences across multiple apps and platforms\
- lack of social accountability and real-world connection\
- difficulty organizing games, training sessions, and events\
- boring and repetitive fitness apps with low engagement\
- limited opportunities to build sports communities and friendships\
\
Desired emotions:\
- excitement\
- motivation\
- momentum\
- achievement\
- competitiveness\
- belonging\
- confidence\
- connection\
- progression\
- social energy\
\
---\
\
# CORE PRODUCT LOOP\
\
Find \uc0\u8594  Match \u8594  Book \u8594  Play \u8594  Repeat\
\
Discover players or coaches\
\uc0\u8594  match or invite\
\uc0\u8594  book venue\
\uc0\u8594  play/train\
\uc0\u8594  earn progress (XP / streaks)\
\uc0\u8594  engage socially (community/events)\
\uc0\u8594  repeat\
\
---\
\
# CORE FEATURES\
\
## 1. Sports Partner Matchmaking\
Key capabilities:\
- player matching by sport and skill\
- nearby player discovery\
- quick game invitations\
- private and public matches\
- player profiles\
- availability matching\
- ratings and reviews system\
\
---\
\
## 2. Coach Discovery & Booking\
Key capabilities:\
- coach profiles and specialties\
- coach search by sport and level\
- training session booking\
- in-app payments\
- ratings and reviews system\
- online and in-person coaching\
\
---\
\
## 3. Venue Discovery & Booking\
Key capabilities:\
- nearby venue discovery\
- real-time availability\
- instant booking\
- group booking coordination\
- integrated payments\
- venue filters by sport and facilities\
- ratings and reviews system\
\
---\
\
## 4. Sports Communities & Events\
Key capabilities:\
- sport-based communities\
- group chats\
- community activity feeds\
- public and private groups\
- event creation and management\
- tournament organization\
- RSVP and attendance tracking\
\
---\
\
## 5. Social Challenges & Gamified Progress\
Key capabilities:\
- streak systems\
- XP and leveling\
- achievement badges\
- leaderboards\
- daily and weekly missions\
- social competitions\
- milestone celebrations\
\
---\
\
# DESIGN PRINCIPLES\
\
We want:\
- Mobile-first experience\
- Fast and low-friction interactions\
- Energetic and uplifting visual identity\
- Sunrise-inspired gradients and lighting atmosphere\
- Emotionally motivating user experiences\
- Minimal and modern UI\
- Bold typography and high-contrast visuals\
- Dopamine-driven feedback loops\
- Seamless matchmaking between players and coaches\
- Frictionless venue booking flows\
- Strong connection between players, coaches, and venues\
- Reduced communication and coordination friction\
- Quick and intuitive navigation\
- Rewarding progression systems\
- Community-driven engagement\
- Scalable ecosystem-oriented product design\
\
Avoid:\
- corporate fitness app aesthetics\
- cluttered and overwhelming interfaces\
- cold or emotionless design\
- overcomplicated booking and coordination flows\
- too many manual communication steps\
- slow matchmaking experiences\
- fragmented user journeys across features\
- old-school gym UI styles\
- feature overload\
- inconsistent navigation\
- low-energy visual design\
- friction-heavy social interactions\
\
---\
\
# TECH STACK\
\
Frontend:\
- React Native\
- Expo\
- TypeScript\
- NativeWind\
- React Navigation\
- Zustand\
\
Backend:\
- Supabase Auth\
- Supabase Database (PostgreSQL)\
- Supabase Edge Functions\
- Supabase Storage\
- Stripe Payments\
\
Infrastructure:\
- vector database\
- recommendation engine\
- real-time notifications\
- geolocation services\
- booking and scheduling system\
- analytics and retention tracking\
- cloud hosting and CDN\
\
---\
\
# BUSINESS MODEL\
\
- free access for players\
- coach booking commissions\
- venue booking commissions\
- community and club event commissions\
- tournament and group activity commissions\
- featured coach and venue promotions\
- premium visibility and discovery tools\
- future brand partnerships and sponsorships\
\
---\
\
# CURRENT PRIORITIES\
\
1. App visual identity and design system development\
2. User onboarding and activation\
3. Sports partner matchmaking experience\
4. Improving retention and social engagement loops\
5. Coach discovery and booking flow\
6. Venue discovery and booking system\
7. Reducing user communication and coordination friction\
8. Community and event engagement\
9. Local network effects and ecosystem growth\
10. Scalable marketplace infrastructure\
